-- Echeverry Wants Colombia Interest Rate Cut Soon, Espectador Says
-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 2012-07-27T14:29:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-27/echeverry-wants-colombia-interest-rate-cut-soon-espectador-says.html
Colombian Finance Minister Juan Carlos Echeverry said the central bank should start to cut
interest rates in the next few months,  El Espectador  reported,
citing an interview with the minister.  Echeverry said a rate cut will be needed in the “coming
months,” the Bogota-based newspaper quoted him as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Bogota at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
